    <teiHeader><fileDesc><titleStmt><title>General Marshall to Executive Headquarters, at Peiping</title></titleStmt><sourceDesc><bibl type="frus-volume-id">frus1946v09</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-id">d503</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-number">503</bibl><bibl type="frus-div-subtype">historical-document</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><profileDesc><settingDesc><setting><date notBefore="1946-06-04T00:00:00-05:00" notAfter="1946-06-04T23:59:59-05:00"/></setting></settingDesc></profileDesc></teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-06-04T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-06-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="503" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d503">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">Marshall Mission Files, Lot 54–D270:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">General <persName type="from">Marshall</persName> to <gloss type="to">Executive Headquarters</gloss>, at Peiping</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Chungking</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-06-04">4 June
                            1946</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>822. The Generalissimo has agreed to the immediate establishment of an advance
                    section of Executive Headquarters in Changchun. General Chou En-lai and I had
                    previously recommended this action. Therefore, please proceed at once to carry
                    out this arrangement with the understanding that the special instructions to
                    govern the function of this advanced section will be issued later.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
